18:02.940 --> 18:04.822
He tempted him with food, right?

18:05.102 --> 18:06.023
A physical need.

18:06.624 --> 18:08.606
He tempted him to test God.

18:09.227 --> 18:14.653
He tempted him with power and authority over all the kingdoms of the world in that moment.

18:14.673 --> 18:19.218
And every time Jesus fought the temptation in the same way, scripture,

18:20.066 --> 18:25.114
He went back to the words of God and said, no, I'm not giving into that.

18:26.015 --> 18:27.958
He continued to trust His heavenly Father.

18:29.140 --> 18:32.866
Along with being tempted, we also see that Jesus was a man of suffering.

18:33.828 --> 18:37.393
If you read through the gospel accounts, you see Jesus suffered a lot.

18:38.896 --> 18:40.638
He suffered relationally.

18:41.760 --> 18:45.426
Jesus experienced betrayal by those in his life.

18:46.018 --> 18:51.945
