18:53.306 --> 18:55.128
Jesus also suffered physically.

18:55.969 --> 19:02.036
He went through the most intense and physical violence that existed in his time and his culture.

19:03.517 --> 19:05.900
Finally, we see that Jesus also suffered spiritually.

19:06.801 --> 19:14.930
On the cross, as he went through that physical pain, he bore the weight, the spiritual weight of our sin on top of that.

19:15.938 --> 19:31.436
We see the Apostle Paul share this in 2 Corinthians chapter five, where it says that God, I mean, he made Jesus who did not know sin to be sin for us, so that in him, we might become the righteousness of God.

19:32.758 --> 19:43.090
Even though that is a glorious reason and promise to us, it came through suffering that Jesus experienced.

19:44.098 --> 19:48.062
Along with that as the son of man, Jesus was like us and that he was often misunderstood.

19:49.624 --> 19:55.390
When people looked at Jesus in the life that he lived, who he spent time with, he was maligned.

19:56.351 --> 19:57.473
