20:05.622 --> 20:13.170
Look at what he said, Matthew 11, the son of man came eating and drinking and they say, look, a glutton and a drunkard.

20:13.858 --> 20:16.681
a friend of tax collectors and sinners.

20:16.701 --> 20:18.283
Do you notice the title that he used there?

20:19.245 --> 20:19.865
The Son of Man.

20:20.967 --> 20:23.330
This is one of the many times he referred to himself in that way.

20:23.370 --> 20:30.238
But what was happening when he was just living his life was the religious leaders would see the people that Jesus spent time with.

20:31.480 --> 20:32.801
And they called him a glutton.

20:33.542 --> 20:34.944
And they called him a drunkard.

20:35.665 --> 20:39.309
Because the people Jesus spent time with the religious leaders would not even go close to.

20:39.349 --> 20:43.154
They wouldn't go close to them because they wanted to remain pure.

20:43.938 --> 20:47.163
They didn't wanna get in the way of their obedience to the law.

20:47.924 --> 20:52.330
But when it came to the tax collectors and sinners, Jesus didn't withdraw.

20:53.552 --> 20:54.333
He engaged.

20:55.174 --> 20:56.436
He went into their homes.

20:57.698 --> 20:58.739
He went to their parties.

20:59.720 --> 21:00.802
He ate with them.

21:01.944 --> 21:03.025
To eat with people.

21:03.686 --> 21:08.112
In this first century, time and culture, it was a sign of friendship.

21:09.635 --> 21:12.018
It was a statement of fellowship.

21:12.610 --> 21:17.057
And Jesus did this with those who were often rejected in his community.

21:18.239 --> 21:23.647
And what happened was people misunderstood him and rejected him.

21:25.109 --> 21:30.056
Finally, as the son of man, Jesus was like us and that he experienced grief.

21:31.398 --> 21:39.090
In our Rif community last week, we just spent time, we recognize that, you know, the holiday season can be one that brings forth grief in us.

21:39.522 --> 21:43.887
Now while many of us are celebrating Christmas and it's a good time, many of us, it's a season of loss.

21:44.808 --> 21:45.909
And so we were thinking about that.

21:46.930 --> 21:55.179
And we looked and we just tried to remember all the times in Scripture that we could of when Jesus experienced grief and we just kept coming up with them.

21:55.199 --> 22:03.388
In John 11, when Jesus is with his friends who were mourning the loss of their brother, Lazarus, and in Jesus just wept.

22:04.749 --> 22:09.394
He wept at how despairing and broken the people were around him

22:09.602 --> 22:12.306
that at loss of the loss of life.

22:13.568 --> 22:25.167
Or when Jesus entered into Jerusalem in the triumphal entry and people are cheering and he is just weeping because the truth of who he was was hidden from them.

22:25.908 --> 22:30.796
They thought he was an earthly king coming to free them now, but he was more than that and he wept.

22:32.299 --> 22:36.786
Or when Jesus experienced separation from God the Father for the first time,

22:37.122 --> 22:41.148
on the cross and he says, my God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

22:42.190 --> 22:49.201
And it's grief, deep sorrow that Jesus experienced.

22:49.221 --> 22:52.726
Because Jesus was and is the son of man.

22:53.728 --> 23:00.178
We see that he was like us, that he experienced humanity in the same ways that we do.

23:01.780 --> 23:05.586
He came from a line of people that were flawed and sinful.

23:05.954 --> 23:06.575
like we are.

23:06.635 --> 23:07.956
He was born to human parents.

23:08.837 --> 23:11.661
He encountered the hardships of being human.

23:12.982 --> 23:17.888
Things like suffering, and temptation, grief, sorrow, being misunderstood.

23:20.190 --> 23:29.701
As we look at these passages and we see all these things about Jesus and His humanity, we actually just shouldn't just leave your thinking, that's really interesting.

23:30.903 --> 23:33.746
We need to take that and we need to put it front and center.

23:34.562 --> 23:36.144
Why does this matter for us?

23:37.545 --> 23:38.707
How should I apply this?

23:39.508 --> 23:44.693
How does knowing Jesus as the Son of Man, why does that impact my life any differently today than any other day?

23:46.275 --> 23:50.720
Well, there's a lot of ways we can apply this to our lives, but there's two I have for us today.

23:51.922 --> 23:56.927
One of them is a truth we should cherish, and the second is an action that we should take.

23:57.788 --> 24:02.834
The first truth is this, because Jesus was and is the Son of Man, that means

24:03.330 --> 24:05.512
Jesus understands you.

24:08.175 --> 24:16.623
The God of the universe knows what it's like to be human because he became like us in our humanity.

24:18.725 --> 24:22.689
Have you ever had someone say to you, I know what you're going through?

24:24.591 --> 24:25.452
It's a powerful thing.

24:26.513 --> 24:28.155
A few weeks ago, I was sick.

24:28.735 --> 24:31.378
I had shingles, which was really unfortunate.

24:31.778 --> 24:35.122
Pastor James came to the West Side venue and he preached in my absence.

24:35.162 --> 24:38.487
And a lot of other people stepped up, which I was so grateful for.

24:38.567 --> 24:42.592
But I was so grateful for the many prayers of many of you, the messages that I got.

24:42.612 --> 24:46.257
But some of the messages said, hey, I have had shingles before.

24:46.297 --> 24:48.640
I know what you're going through.

24:49.841 --> 24:53.906
And while I was really thankful for all the messages and the well wishes, like those ones encouraged me differently.

24:54.687 --> 24:56.350
Because I would just reply with, I'm sorry.

24:57.091 --> 24:58.352
You know, it's now fun.

24:58.412 --> 24:59.794
You know that, right?

25:00.034 --> 25:01.636
But there was a shared experience.

25:02.557 --> 25:03.278
They understood.

25:03.338 --> 25:17.094
And while having the same life experiences, it's not a prerequisite to care for people or to be there or be present, it is a uniquely powerful thing because they know, they understand you.

25:18.756 --> 25:23.602
In all the difficulties that we go through in our human lives, Jesus can actually say this to us.

25:25.124 --> 25:27.186
I know what you are going through.

25:29.314 --> 25:34.181
Jesus can sympathize with you and your suffering and your pain.

25:35.944 --> 25:41.452
Human suffering is one of the worst challenges we ever encounter in our lives.

25:42.353 --> 25:53.389
A recent study showed how human suffering, it's one of the top reasons why followers of Jesus doubt their faith or why they experience doubt, those questions that linger on.

25:53.610 --> 25:56.194
Because of my suffering, God, is he really good?

25:56.254 --> 25:59.218
Is God there at all?

26:00.034 --> 26:01.716
If he is, why isn't he doing anything?

26:02.917 --> 26:06.402
We ask those questions in suffering and they cause us to doubt.

26:08.063 --> 26:09.265
Jesus gets it.

26:10.807 --> 26:14.711
In his deity, he did not keep himself from the difficult aspects of being human.

26:15.933 --> 26:17.134
He fully embraced them.

26:17.955 --> 26:27.186
And because that's true, he modeled for us what it looks like to suffer well, to suffer with a deep dependence upon his heavenly father.

26:28.546 --> 26:31.911
Jesus can sympathize with you in your suffering.

26:33.934 --> 26:36.619
Jesus also understands you in your temptations to sin.

26:36.679 --> 26:45.452
Hebrews 218 tells us that because Jesus was tempted in every way, he's able to help us in our temptation.

26:47.976 --> 26:56.850
One of the greatest lies the devil wants to convince you of in your Christian life is that you are alone in your temptation

26:57.314 --> 27:05.124
and in your fight against sin, that your temptations are worse than what others experience, that no one would understand you.

27:06.545 --> 27:19.441
Because when you begin to believe that, instead of pursuing God being known by Him and confessing, you isolate and you keep yourself from other people.

27:21.243 --> 27:26.610
Jesus knows your struggle more than you would ever be able to communicate to Him.

27:27.810 --> 27:35.963
And even with that knowledge he has of your temptations, of your sins, he will not let go of you.

27:37.906 --> 27:45.098
If you are a Christian, you are his and he's promised to keep you in his hand forever.

27:47.021 --> 27:49.605
Jesus understands you and your temptations to sin.

27:51.508 --> 27:55.154
Jesus also understands you when you're misunderstood by others.

27:56.450 --> 28:00.856
As a Christian, there's gonna be ways that you live your life that are different than the world around you.

28:02.058 --> 28:03.339
You're gonna spend your time differently.

28:04.281 --> 28:07.665
You're gonna have relationships with people that others may question.

28:08.967 --> 28:13.553
You're gonna steward your money and your resources for the glory of God instead of yourself.

28:15.096 --> 28:17.379
And in doing that, people aren't gonna get it.

28:17.399 --> 28:20.283
They're gonna be like, why are you doing that?

28:21.124 --> 28:25.650
Even members of your own family who don't share your faith, they may not get you.

28:27.394 --> 28:28.235
Jesus gets you.

28:29.577 --> 28:33.183
He understands what it means to be misunderstood.

28:33.243 --> 28:35.666
And he will encourage you.

28:36.307 --> 28:37.509
And he will bring you joy in that.

28:37.529 --> 28:37.950
You know why?

28:37.970 --> 28:41.295
Because you look more like him than the world around you.

28:42.917 --> 28:44.700
Jesus understands when you're misunderstood.

28:46.382 --> 28:50.268
Finally, Jesus understands you in the grief that you experience.

28:52.291 --> 28:54.314
Grief is not a sign of unbelief.

28:55.876 --> 28:57.138
It's not a lack of faith.

28:58.050 --> 28:59.592
It's not a sin to be repented of.

29:00.773 --> 29:06.500
And we know this because the one who was without sin, Jesus himself, grieved.

29:08.062 --> 29:09.444
He was a man of sorrows.

29:11.647 --> 29:21.118
So as you process loss, as you grieve, as you walk through difficult seasons, you can do so knowing that God knows.

29:22.500 --> 29:25.063
He knows what you need more than you do.

29:26.044 --> 29:27.506
And not only does he know,

29:27.874 --> 29:30.898
but he is a good Father who will provide you with what you need.

29:33.080 --> 29:45.935
Cherish this truth today that you are understood by the God of the universe in your humanity and what you experience in the past and what you will experience in the future.

29:48.198 --> 29:50.361
But we're not just gonna sit and cherish that truth.

29:50.441 --> 29:55.026
That truth should lead us to doing something, an action that we should take

29:55.938 --> 30:03.347
Because Jesus is the Son of man, and he understands us in our humanity, we should draw near to him.

30:05.069 --> 30:08.073
Approach him with boldness whenever it is needed.

30:09.115 --> 30:22.592
We see this encouragement in the book of Hebrews, chapter four, verse 15, for we do not have a high priest who is unable to sympathize with us in our weaknesses, but one who has been tempted in every way as we are, yet without sin.

30:23.853 --> 30:24.594
Therefore,

30:25.058 --> 30:37.130
or in light of that, or because that is true, let us approach the throne of grace with boldness so that we may receive mercy and find grace to help us in time of need.

30:39.372 --> 30:46.680
The picture I have in my head of this verse is when a child runs up to their mom or their dad when they're hurt.

30:47.901 --> 30:49.442
This happens a lot in our house.

30:50.163 --> 30:53.106
We've got two young boys, but in that moment,

30:53.794 --> 30:58.359
That child isn't going back and forth in their mind about whether or not they should find mom or dad.

30:59.821 --> 31:03.064
They're not asking the question, does dad have time for me?

31:03.084 --> 31:05.066
Is mom busy?

31:05.086 --> 31:06.728
Am I interrupting?

31:06.748 --> 31:08.650
Am I gonna be in trouble?

31:09.651 --> 31:09.912
No.

31:09.952 --> 31:13.636
Instead, they boldly approach.

31:14.777 --> 31:17.200
They run to their mom or dad.

31:18.661 --> 31:22.866
Not only because their mom or dad can help them, but because they want to.

31:23.938 --> 31:25.139
That's their safe place.

31:27.322 --> 31:29.264
What if we approached Jesus like that?

31:30.846 --> 31:51.730
In the times of our life when we need help, when we're tempted, when we're suffering, when we're lost, when we're grieving, when we don't know what to do, what if we approached the throne of grace with boldness, fully expecting to receive mercy and grace in our time of need?

31:53.698 --> 31:55.661
We don't have to wonder if that's what we're gonna get.

31:57.283 --> 31:57.944
It's promised.

31:59.126 --> 32:02.811
This is available to us because the work Jesus has done through the gospel.

32:03.191 --> 32:07.638
He made a way for us through his life, death, and resurrection.

32:09.180 --> 32:12.885
Over and over again in the gospels, this is what Jesus said.

32:13.125 --> 32:17.051
This is what he came to do as the son of man.

32:18.593 --> 32:22.098
Look at some of the times Jesus mentioned himself as the son of man.

32:22.594 --> 32:27.880
In Luke chapter 19, this is what Jesus said to a sinner who had turned to him in repentance.

32:27.900 --> 32:29.141
This is the story of Zacchaeus.

32:31.003 --> 32:34.147
Jesus said this, today salvation has come to this house.

32:34.847 --> 32:37.390
Jesus told him because he too is a son of Abraham.

32:38.071 --> 32:42.496
For the son of man has come to seek and save the lost.

32:44.318 --> 32:51.666
Every single one of us, when we come into this world as sons and daughters, we're spiritually lost.

32:52.194 --> 32:52.815
and our sin.

32:54.337 --> 33:01.086
Our relationship with God is fractured due to our sin nature, and it cannot be repaired by our own righteous works or deeds.

33:01.146 --> 33:04.270
It can only be repaired by being found.

33:05.752 --> 33:07.254
By coming to Jesus in faith.

33:08.937 --> 33:16.928
In Mark chapter 10, Jesus said something similar to his disciples, and he said this to them after they had been debating out which one of them were the greatest disciple.

33:17.729 --> 33:18.430
They were missing it.

33:19.131 --> 33:21.714
And Jesus said this in Mark 10 verse 45,

33:22.338 --> 33:30.167
For even the Son of Man did not come to be served but to serve and to give His life as a ransom for many.

33:32.069 --> 33:33.290
This is why Jesus came.

33:35.633 --> 33:43.642
To give His life as a ransom for us, and He would do so when He would take the sins of the world on to Himself and die on a cross.

33:44.603 --> 33:47.046
His life would pay the sinful debt that we owed.

33:48.908 --> 33:51.090
Finally, right before Jesus was crucified,

33:51.938 --> 33:55.743
He was asked explicitly, are you the Messiah?

33:57.125 --> 33:58.106
And this is how he answered.

33:58.146 --> 33:59.328
He answered the high priest.

34:01.010 --> 34:04.595
Mark 14 verse 62, he said, I am, said Jesus.

34:05.516 --> 34:12.987
And you will see the son of man seated at the right hand of power and coming with the clouds of heaven.

34:15.109 --> 34:18.514
As Jesus answered the high priest who was about to sentence him to death,

34:19.138 --> 34:22.302
He not only affirmed the truth of who he was, but do you know how he did so?

34:24.185 --> 34:25.086
With the prophecy.

34:26.468 --> 34:28.050
That's Daniel chapter seven.

34:29.873 --> 34:33.197
The high priest would have known what Jesus was saying.

34:33.738 --> 34:37.243
And we see this in the next verse, the high priest he tears his robes.

34:38.725 --> 34:40.447
That's the last thing he needs to hear.

34:41.088 --> 34:41.549
You know why?

34:41.589 --> 34:43.892
Because Jesus is saying, it's me.

34:43.932 --> 34:48.498
I am the one you've been waiting for.

34:49.346 --> 34:50.668
I'm the one from the vision.

34:52.110 --> 34:52.731
It's me.

34:55.295 --> 35:17.266
This is who Jesus is, the Son of Man, the one we celebrate every single Christmas, the one who entered the world like us, who experienced humanity like us, the highs, the lows, the hardships and the joys.

35:18.594 --> 35:25.584
The one who entered the world to make a way for us, to know God and be known by Him.

35:28.469 --> 35:37.021
Because that is true, cherish the truth that God understands you in your humanity.

35:37.101 --> 35:40.366
Let that draw you toward Him today.

35:41.748 --> 35:45.554
But not only that, let that truth

35:46.242 --> 35:51.669
encourage you to approach Him boldly in every time of need that you have.

35:52.691 --> 35:57.117
Because when you do so, you will receive mercy and grace and abundance.

35:58.679 --> 35:59.140
Let's pray.

36:02.044 --> 36:08.973
Heavenly Father, I thank You that You sent us a Savior.

36:11.396 --> 36:15.442
God, as we sing the songs and as we open the scriptures, we are just in awe

36:15.554 --> 36:17.336
of your plan to do that.

36:19.740 --> 36:26.749
God, I take so much encouragement in knowing that Jesus understands us in our humanity.

36:28.472 --> 36:34.199
God, there's been times in my life where I have just been so encouraged by another person who has said, I know what you're going through.

36:34.880 --> 36:38.325
And Jesus can say that to us in our lives.

36:41.329 --> 36:45.074
Father, we're so grateful for Christmas

36:47.618 --> 36:52.344
that you entered in, you came near.

36:54.046 --> 37:01.415
Lord, as we sing the songs, as we open the scriptures, let us cherish those truths.

37:03.057 --> 37:08.244
Now while Jesus was the Son of God, he is the Son of God, he also is the Son of man.

37:09.585 --> 37:10.226
He was human.

37:13.450 --> 37:14.251
Lord, we thank you.

37:15.312 --> 37:16.594
We cherish that truth.

37:17.538 --> 37:40.584
And Lord, I just pray that you help us cherish that truth, but also have it lead us to approaching you in our times of need instead of isolating and keeping ourselves away from you, Lord, but to run to you like a child running to their mom or dad, to approach you boldly expecting to receive mercy and grace.

37:42.967 --> 37:45.490
In Jesus' name that we pray, amen.

